---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { site } from '../data/content';

const updated = 'July 2026';
---

<Base
  title={`Privacy — ${site.name}`}
  description="How this site handles data. No cookies, no tracking, no personal profiling — just anonymous, aggregate analytics."
>
  <section class="section legal">
    <div class="wrap legal__wrap">
      <p class="section__label">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="legal__title">Privacy &amp; data</h1>
      <p class="legal__updated">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <p class="legal__lead">
        This site is built to respect your privacy. It sets no cookies, shows no ads, and never
        tries to identify you or follow you around the web. Here’s exactly what happens when you
        visit.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        I use <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare
        Web Analytics</a>, a privacy-first, <strong>cookieless</strong> service. It measures only
        anonymous, aggregate information — such as page views, the country a visit comes from, and
        which site referred you. It does <strong>not</strong> use cookies, does not fingerprint your
        device, and cannot identify you or track you across other websites.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site stores <strong>no cookies</strong> on your device. That’s why you won’t see a
        cookie banner — there’s nothing to consent to.
      </p>

      <h2>If you email me</h2>
      <p>
        If you reach out at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>, I use your message and
        contact details only to reply to you. I don’t add you to any mailing list and I don’t share
        your information with anyone.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        The site is hosted on Netlify, which — like any web host — may process standard technical
        request logs (such as IP addresses) to serve pages and keep the site secure. These logs are
        not used to profile visitors.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under Swiss (nFADP) and EU (GDPR) data-protection law you have rights over any personal data
        relating to you. Since this site doesn’t build visitor profiles, there’s very little to act
        on — but if you have any question about privacy here, just write to
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> and I’ll be glad to help.
      </p>

      <p class="legal__back"><a href="/">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal__wrap {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .legal__title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3.2rem);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .legal__updated {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .legal__lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.4vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 2.2rem 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .legal p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--border-strong);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.25s ease;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--text);
  }
  .legal__back {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal__back a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
